<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="O" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Ourself" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Ourself</orth> (two words in O. Edd.), == myself, in the regal style: <bibl n="shak. mm 1.1.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 1, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.1.86" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 1, 86</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.1.169" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 169</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.196" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 196</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.6.104" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 6, 104</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.1.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 1, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 3.1.42" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 1, 42</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.2.122" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 2, 122</bibl> etc. Used by other persons in general maxims: <cit><quote>we cannot weigh our brother with o.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 2.2.126" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 2, 126</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>learning is but an adjunct to o.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.314" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 314</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>